eternity /ɪˈtɜːnɪtɪ/

N-UNCOUNT Eternity is time without an end or a state of existence outside time, especially the state that some people believe they will pass into after they have died. 永恒; 永存 

例： I have always found the thought of eternity terrifying. 我总觉得永生的想法很可怕。 

2. N-SING If you say that a situation lasted for an eternity , you mean that it seemed to last an extremely long time, usually because it was boring or unpleasant. 极长的时间 

例： The war continued for an eternity. 那场战争持续了极长的时间。

